  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-intensive CFD pipeline)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The simulation pipeline is built on a multi-component software stack: a Python-based pre-processing module that generates boundary condition files, ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 as the RANS CFD solver, a custom C++ post-processing library that integrates the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model across Lagrangian particle trajectories, and a MATLAB orchestration layer that aggregates results across the five flow-speed operating points. All solver runs completed nominally. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
