      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — nominal completion",
      "description": "Planar PIV measurements at three axial planes were compared against RANS-predicted velocity magnitudes. All five operating points completed nominal solver runs. Mean relative error in velocity magnitude was 6.3% across measurement planes. No solver interruptions or output anomalies were recorded."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-pressure-rise",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-rise validation — nominal completion",
      "description": "Predicted pressure rise across the pump at each of the five flow-speed combinations was compared against bench-top hydraulic measurements. All CFD runs completed to convergence with residuals below 1e-5. Predicted values fell within 4.1% of experimental means. Solver output files were parsed by the C++ post-processor without exception."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-hemolysis-rh",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) validation — nominal completion",
      "description": "RH values computed by the Lagrangian hemolysis post-processor were compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements using a modified ASTM F1841 protocol. The MATLAB orchestration layer aggregated particle-trajectory outputs from all operating points. All pipeline stages completed nominally. RH predictions were within the 95% prediction interval of experimental data at four of five operating points; the fifth point showed 8% overprediction, conservatively bounding the clinical risk estimate."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-04-mesh-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (2.1 M, 5.4 M, 11.2 M cells) were evaluated. Grid convergence index (GCI) for RH at the worst-case operating point was 3.8%, below the 5% threshold. All solver instances completed nominal runs. The 5.4 M cell mesh was selected for production runs."
    }
